## Phase 3 — Layout Architecture

Enterprise sites use **structural clarity**. Every region has a job.

### Page Anatomy (for marketing/landing pages)
```
[NAV]         — sticky, transparent→solid on scroll, max-width 1200px, 72px tall
[HERO]        — full-viewport or 80vh, single headline, one CTA, supporting visual
[SOCIAL PROOF]— logos or testimonials, muted treatment
[FEATURES]    — 3–4 primary capabilities, icon + headline + 1–2 lines
[DEEP DIVE]   — alternating text+visual, product screenshots
[PRICING]     — clear tiers, recommended tier highlighted
[CTA BANNER]  — final conversion section
[FOOTER]      — organized columns, legal, social
```

### Grid system
- **Max content width**: 1200px (or 1280px) centered
- **Column grid**: 12-column, 24px gutters on desktop; 4-column on mobile
- **Section padding**: `var(--space-24)` top/bottom (96px), tighter on mobile
- **Text columns**: Body text max 65ch (characters) wide — never full-width prose

### Responsive breakpoints
```css
/* mobile-first */
/* sm: 640px | md: 768px | lg: 1024px | xl: 1280px */
```

---

## Phase 4 — Component Rules

### Navigation
- Logo left, links center (or left), CTA button right
- Active state: subtle underline or background, never bold weight change alone
- Mobile: hamburger → slide-in drawer, never a dropdown stack

### Buttons
```css
/* Primary */
background: var(--color-brand);
color: white;
padding: 10px 20px (small) | 12px 24px (default) | 14px 28px (large);
border-radius: var(--radius-md);
font-weight: 500;
transition: all 150ms ease;
/* hover: brightness(1.1) + shadow-md */

/* Secondary */
background: transparent;
border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
/* hover: background surface-2 */

/* Ghost */
background: transparent; no border;
/* hover: background surface-2 */
```

### Cards
- Always use `var(--shadow-md)` or border, never both unless intentional
- `border-radius: var(--radius-lg)`
- Internal padding: `var(--space-6)` minimum
- Hover: translate(-2px) + shadow-lg, 200ms ease

### Forms
- Labels above inputs, never floating
- Input height: 40px (default), 36px (dense), 48px (prominent)
- Focus: brand-color border + subtle outer glow
- Error: red border + inline message below, never alert boxes

### Icons
- Lucide, Heroicons, or Phosphor — never emoji as UI icons
- Size: 16px (inline/dense), 20px (default), 24px (feature icons)
- Stroke weight consistent across entire UI (1.5px for most)

---

## Phase 5 — Motion & Interaction

**Less is more. Enterprise sites are calm, not flashy.**

### Transition timing
```css
--ease-out: cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);   /* elements entering */
--ease-in:  cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 1, 1);        /* elements leaving */
--ease-default: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1); /* most interactions */

/* Durations */
--duration-fast:   100ms; /* hover states, toggles */
--duration-default: 200ms; /* most transitions */
--duration-slow:   350ms; /* page elements, modals */
--duration-enter:  500ms; /* hero animations, page load */
```

### What to animate (and what not to)
- Animate: scroll reveals (fade+translate), hover states, button feedback, modal entrance, number counting
- Never animate: layout shifts, text color on hover (unless link), continuous loops on important content

### Scroll reveals (use sparingly — only for key sections)
```css
@keyframes fadeUp {
  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(16px); }
  to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}
/* Trigger with IntersectionObserver, delay children with animation-delay */
```

