## Phase 6 — Visual Craft

These details separate good from exceptional:

### Backgrounds
Never plain white or #000. Always add depth:
- **Light**: `#FAFAFA` or `#F8F8F7` base; cards at `#FFFFFF` with border
- **Dark**: `#0A0A0A` or `#09090B` base; cards at `#111111` or `#18181B`
- **Gradient backgrounds**: radial gradients at 5–15% opacity, positioned off-center
- **Noise texture**: `filter: url(#noise)` SVG filter at 3–5% opacity for warmth
- **Grid/dot patterns**: CSS background-image at very low opacity for technical products

### Border treatment
```css
/* Light mode */
border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);

/* Dark mode */
border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);

/* Gradient border (premium feel) */
border: 1px solid transparent;
background: linear-gradient(surface, surface) padding-box,
            linear-gradient(135deg, brand-color, transparent) border-box;
```

### Glassmorphism (use intentionally, not everywhere)
```css
background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
```

### Number/stat display
Large metrics deserve display treatment:
```css
font-family: var(--font-display);
font-size: clamp(48px, 6vw, 96px);
font-weight: 600;
letter-spacing: -0.03em;
line-height: 1;
```

---

## Phase 7 — Accessibility & Performance

Enterprise sites must be accessible. Non-negotiable:
- Color contrast: 4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for large text/UI
- Focus indicators: visible, 2px offset, brand color
- `aria-label` on icon-only buttons
- Semantic HTML: `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<footer>`
- Image `alt` attributes always present and descriptive

Performance signals of quality:
- CSS custom properties for all tokens (no hardcoded values in components)
- No inline styles unless dynamically computed
- Lazy load images below the fold
- Font display: swap

---

## Phase 8 — Copywriting Standards

Enterprise-grade copy is:
- **Specific, not vague**: "Deploy in 3 minutes" not "Get started quickly"
- **Outcome-first**: Lead with what the user gets, not what the product does
- **Confident, not salesy**: State facts, let them convince
- **Short**: Headlines under 10 words. Subheadlines under 20 words.

Headlines follow the pattern: [Verb] + [Outcome] (+ [Differentiator])
> "Ship faster. Sleep better." / "The design tool for teams that ship." / "Payments infrastructure for the internet."

---

## Output Requirements

1. **Complete, runnable code** — no TODOs, no placeholders like "// add content here"
2. **Real placeholder content** — realistic copy, not "Lorem ipsum"
3. **Fully responsive** — works at 375px and 1440px
4. **Single file** for HTML artifacts, unless user requests separation
5. **State your design decisions** — 2–3 sentences explaining your palette, font, and energy choices before the code
6. **No stock photo URLs** — use CSS-generated visuals, SVG illustrations, or gradient placeholders for images

### Google Fonts import pattern (for HTML artifacts)
```html
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=FONTNAME:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
```

### Font recommendations by brand energy
| Energy | Display | Body |
|---|---|---|
| Minimal/surgical | Geist, Syne | Geist, DM Sans |
| Warm/human | Fraunces, Lora | Plus Jakarta Sans, Nunito |
| Bold/editorial | Syne, Unbounded | Outfit, Barlow |
| Technical/developer | JetBrains Mono (accents) | Inter (only here), IBM Plex Sans |
| Luxury/refined | Cormorant Garamond, Playfair | Jost, Raleway |
| Institutional | Cabinet Grotesk | Instrument Sans |
